Examples to start STILT runs

./start.stilt.sh <station-id> <latitude> <longitude> <altitude> <startdate> <enddate> <run-id> <parts> <cprun>

e.g.
./start.stilt.sh HEI 49.42 8.67 30 20140601 20140601 UHEI 1 1

all parameters need to be specified, no default

station-id: ususally letter code (3-6 letters)

latitude: decimal degree, positive values for north and negative values for south 

longitude: decimal degree, positive values for east and negative values for west 

startdate: year month day in format YYYYMMDD

enddate: year month day in format YYYYMMDD

run-id: letter code to separate users

cprun: select type of stilt run 
  0: only prepare list of time slots
  1: use only existing particle location files for calculation on icos-cp.eu to prepare files for footprint tool
  2: allow full STILT run


